  \"rxn_008\": 0.9,\n        \"rxn_009\": 0.84,\n        \"rxn_010\": 0.86\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.82,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.84,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.92,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.88,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.84,\n      \"feedback\": \"This variant improves network interconnection by sourcing reduced carbon hydrothermally before entering surface cyanosulfidic chemistry, but the hydrothermal formate branch is not actually necessary for the arginine core sequence. The core chemistry remains literature-grounded, while the added hydrothermal feed introduces modest speculative overhead without breaking plausibility.\",\n      \"approved\": true,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\n        \"rxn_003\",\n        \"rxn_001\"\n      ],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Demonstrate how hydrothermal formate materially feeds the cyanosulfidic branch instead of serving as a disconnected scaffold\",\n        \"Use literature-supported vent conditions conservatively because arginine itself is thermolabile\",\n        \"Retain the route as a network variant rather than a direct experimentally validated synthesis\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P3\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_003\": 0.6,\n        \"rxn_015\": 0.58,\n        \"rxn_011\": 0.82\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.68,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.78,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.72,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.82,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.74,\n      \"feedback\": \"Direct ornithine guanylation by cyanamide is conceptually strong and directly reflects the best alternate literature route, but the network overstates ornithine synthesis by representing it as a direct HCN + NH3 product. The final guanylation step is chemically plausible, yet prebiotic one-pot validation is lacking and ornithine sourcing is the major weakness.\",\n      \"approved\": false,\n      \"problematic_reactio